The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                Five persons were arrested on Thursday in connection with the collapse of the basement and the first floor of a mall under construction in Kazipara, Howrah, on Wednesday night. The five were produced in court on Thursday and granted bail. They were supervising the project and supplying building material. The Howrah mayor, Gopal Mukherjee, has constituted a committee to look into the cause of the collapse.    A 35-year-old constable of the Calcutta traffic guard, Biren Sil, died after being knocked down by a vehicle on Ambedkar Setu, in Tiljala, on Thursday. Police said Sil, a resident of Cooch Behar, was taken to RN Tagore Institute of Cardiac Sciences, where he died.    Three persons were arrested from Sonarpur, on the southern fringes of the city, on Thursday for forcibly collecting subscriptions for Durga puja. Police said the youths were stopping lorries that were carrying vegetables and fish to city markets and demanding money.    The South Eastern Railway will add extra coaches to 14 pairs of express trains between September 30 and November 4. Extra coaches will be added to the Howrah-Hatia Express, Howrah-Hyderabad East Coast Express, Shalimar-Digha Express and the Howrah-Digha Express. The Howrah-Sambalpur Koraput Express and the Howrah-Tatanagar Steel Express will get an extra AC two-tier coach and an AC chair car coach, respectively.    Manik Paik, 49, was arrested on Thursday for offering a police constables job to a youth in South 24-Parganas in exchange for Rs 1.9 lakh. Paik was trying to settle the deal in Alipore when he was arrested.    Five students of Kamrabad High School of Sonarpur were questioned on Thursday after two youths allegedly came to their school and promised to teach them how to make bombs. The boys were later released.    Kalpana Rai, 40, was arrested after being caught carrying 17 gram of heroin in Narkeldanga on Thursday morning.                                                                                                                                                                 
